byline.original: By KEITH BRADSHER and JANE PERLEZ

headline.main: Is Trump Serious About Trade War? China’s Leaders Hunt for Answers
headline.print_headline: Shifting Signals On Trade Baffle China’s Leaders

lead_paragraph: Some of the most powerful men in China have been seeking out experts to gain a better understanding of how to respond to President Trump’s combative trade agenda.
snippet: Some of the most powerful men in China have been seeking out experts to gain a better understanding of how to respond to President Trump’s combative trade agenda.

headline.main: Tech Firms Sign ‘Digital Geneva Accord’ Not to Aid Governments in Cyberwar

lead_paragraph: The companies, including Microsoft and Facebook, hope to create a Geneva Conventions for cyberspace, but none are from countries that are suspected in most of the recent attacks.

headline.main: Qualcomm May Be Collateral Damage in a U.S.-China Trade War
headline.print_headline: Chip Maker Finds Itself Trapped in the Middle  As Trading Rivals Spar

lead_paragraph: One of the technology industry’s brightest stars finds its business under fire in two countries. Beijing seeks new concessions to seal a major deal.

headline.main: G.E. Makes a Sharp ‘Pivot’ on Digital
headline.print_headline: Finding Challenges Daunting, G.E. Scales Back Its Lofty Digital Ambitions

lead_paragraph: The industrial giant plunged into internet-era software with gusto. But it has trimmed back after finding that becoming a tech player is daunting and costly.

headline.main: Workers of Silicon Valley, It’s Time to Organize
headline.print_headline: Workers In Tech, Use The Force

lead_paragraph: Employees in the tech industry have an unusual power: They can make their companies act more responsibly. All they have to do is speak up.
